Change Request CR-00001: DOCSYS Revision Checklist

Description

A structured operator-grade checklist for updating all DOCSYS and L‑Class Pages

This change request formalizes a.                  DOCSYS Revision Checklist as the operative checklist for updating all DOCSYS and L-Class Pages. It ensures alignment with the updated identity-assignment rule and the clarified separation between the Ide             Architecture and the Record Architecture.

Scope

Updating DOCSYS governance

Adding new document classes

Revising identity rules

Auditing consistency across Pages

1. Purpose

This checklist provides a step-by-step sequence for revising all DOCSYS and L‑Class Pages to align with the updated identity‑assignment rule and the clarified separation between the Identity Architecture and the Record Architecture.

Use this checklist whenever:

Updating DOCSYS governance

Adding new document classes

Revising identity rules

Auditing consistency across Pages

2. Identity Rule Integration

2.1 Confirm DOC ID Assignment Rule

Insert or verify the rule:

“New DOC IDs are assigned by finding the highest number with the corresponding prefix and incrementing it by 1.”

Ensure rule appears in P‑00000

Ensure rule appears in X‑00001

Ensure rule is referenced in all DOCSYS Pages that mention identity

2.2 Validate Class-Scoped Numbering

Confirm each class (P, W, R, A, D, CR, X) has its own numbering stream

Confirm numbering begins at <ClassPrefix>-00000 for templates

Confirm numbering increments sequentially

Confirm no DOC ID is reused or repurposed

3. L‑Class Separation

3.1 Clarify L‑Class Exclusion

Add statement that L‑Class does not follow DOCSYS numbering rules

Confirm L‑Class identifiers are described as semantic and domain‑encoded

Ensure L‑Class is placed in the Record Architecture, not Identity Architecture

3.2 Validate L‑Class Index

Confirm GAAP accounts are listed correctly

Confirm system codes and runtime events are categorized

Confirm no DOCSYS numbering rules appear in L‑Class sections

4. Cross-References

4.1 Reference P‑00000

Add cross‑reference to P‑00000 in all Pages that describe DOC ID assignment

4.2 Reference X‑00001

Add cross‑reference to X‑00001 in Pages describing DOCSYS hierarchy or class structure

4.3 Reference L‑Class Governance

Add cross‑reference to L‑Class Governance Page where Record Architecture is discussed

5. Page-Specific Updates

5.1 P‑00000 — DOCSYS Document Creation Governance

Confirm identity‑assignment rule is present

Confirm DOCSYS class definitions are correct

Confirm AUID and UDIS rules are accurate

5.2 X‑00001 — DOCSYS Index Hierarchy Governance

Insert identity‑assignment rule

Confirm hierarchy reflects updated architecture

Confirm L‑Class is excluded from DOCSYS numbering

5.3 L‑Class Governance Page

Insert explicit exclusion from DOCSYS numbering

Confirm semantic nature of L‑Class identifiers

Confirm crosswalk references are correct

5.4 DOCSYS Document Identity Index

Confirm all DOC IDs follow sequential numbering

Confirm templates use 00000

Confirm no numbering gaps unless intentional

6. Consistency Audit

6.1 Identity Architecture

DOC ID rules consistent across all Pages

AUID rules consistent across all Pages

UDIS rules consistent across all Pages

6.2 Record Architecture

L‑Class consistently treated as semantic

No identity‑pure rules applied to L‑Class

6.3 Crosswalks

X‑Class documents reference correct namespaces

L‑Class mappings appear only in X‑Class

7. Final Verification

All Pages updated

All cross‑references correct

All numbering consistent

All governance language aligned with UNISYS architecture

